CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1961, page 19, reads: "GOP Dinner - When Allegheny County Republicans stages their Lincoln dinner on Feb. 11, Governor John A. Volpe of Massachusetts, while president John F. Kennedy was sweeping the state by more than half-a-million votes. Governor Volpe (center) is shown chatting with Commissioner John M. Walker (left). Looking on are the Rev. LeRoy Patrick (standing left) and William pg. Young (right). - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Two men standing and shaking hands, including one on left wearing eyeglasses, moustache, light colored shirt, diamond patterned necktie, and dark suit with light colored handkerchief in left breast pocket, gathered in interior with abstract patterned rug and light colored curtains for the Allegheny County Republican Lincoln Dinner
